# High-Performance Streaming & Low-Latency YOLO Inference Plan

This implementation plan details the optimizations required to eliminate video stream lag and stuttering across the Sand Mining Detection dashboard and pipeline systems. By decoupling heavy network I/O and CPU-bound YOLO inference from frame acquisition, we will achieve fluid, real-time 30 FPS video streaming.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Key Architectural Improvements:**
> 1. **Event-Driven MJPEG Streaming:** We will replace uvicorn's polling-based `await asyncio.sleep(0.06)` stream generator with a highly reactive `asyncio.Event` trigger. The server will stream a frame to the browser the exact millisecond it is captured or analyzed, rather than spinning on a timer.
> 2. **Decoupled Server-Side YOLO:** In Webcam/Edge Mode, the `/api/edge/frame` HTTP POST handler will return `{"status": "ok"}` immediately after receiving the frame (taking under 2ms). Inference will run asynchronously in uvicorn's background thread, preventing YOLO from bottlenecking HTTP request completion.
> 3. **Queue-Based Pipeline Uploading:** We will add a thread-safe dropping queue and background worker to `WebcamPipeline` and `EdgePipeline`. The frame capture loop will read the camera fluidly (30 FPS) and drop frames into the queue. The background uploader will stream them without blocking camera capture.

